Photo by and machines on UnsplashThis morning, after doing my company’s accounting and getting upset again at how garbage that software is, I decided I needed an easy, little coding task to chill 😄. So I added a small progress bar to the top of my blog posts. It’s a nice little cosmetic win, and I thought I would follow up with a short post to share a couple of beginner friendly details.
The component
To add this new element to the blog I created a component. I might not reuse it elsewhere, but still, it’s always nice to approach composition with agnostic, reusable components. It takes an anchor element (the end of the article) as a property, since we are looking to show the progression of the reading, computes this percentage, and renders it in a <progress> element pinned at the top.
